.env
.env.*
# Defense-in-depth: the two patterns above are ROOT-anchored and miss nested env files
# (e.g. frontend/.env.local, external/**/.env). Exclude env files at ANY depth so a real
# secret can never bake into the PUBLIC prakharojha/conclave image via `COPY . .`.
**/.env
**/.env.*
# Large reference subtree not used by the API at runtime (Shape-OS integration ref; also
# carries its own .env.example files) — keep it out of the image entirely.
external/
__pycache__
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache
tests/
.git
.gitignore
client/
docs/
plans/
*.md
# Local dev state — never bake into the image. The named volume in
# docker-compose persists production data; baking dev SQLite would leak
# local test submissions into the prod image.
data/*.db
data/*.db-*
data/mock_ideas/submissions.jsonl
.venv/
venv/
node_modules/
